content: Got it on iPhone as well. Goes beyond the free version which is similar to Torres... this version calculates ALL of the port area. The free version and Torres calculates using the internal dimensions of the port, but what about the .75 volume the port takes up inside the box? This app takes everything into account. This is top notch. So my box made to 2.0ft3 @32hz using Torres is actually 1.92ish @34.5hz, but if I swap in a bigger subwoofer, it takes it down to 1.87ft3 @36hz. Time to rebuild üëç
